        "logic_source": "Core Islamic Knowledge",
        "logic_authenticity": "",
        "logic_statement": "The term \"Islam\" (الإسلام) comes from the Arabic root word \"س-ل-م\" (S-L-M), which carries meanings of:\n1. Peace\n2. Submission\n3. Surrender\n4. Obedience\n\n<b>Actual Meaning of \"Islam\"</b>\nIslam means \"<b>submission to the will of Allah (God)</b>\" with <i>sincerity</i>, <i>obedience</i>, and <i>peace</i>.\n\n<b>In simple terms:</b>\n<li>A person who follows Islam submits himself or herself fully to the guidance of Allah.</li><li>Through this submission, one finds inner peace, and contributes to peace in society.</li>",
