    {
        "title": "2",
        "question": "What is the meaning of “Tawheed”?",
        "chain_of_narrator": "",
        "authentic_hadith": "",
        "authentic_hadith_arabic": "",
        "clear_answer": "",
        "clear_answer_tag": "",
        "reference_number": "",
        "in_book_reference_number": "",
        "verify_on": "",
        "verification_method": "",
        "logic_source": "Core Islamic Knowledge",
        "logic_authenticity": "",
        "logic_statement": "The word <b>Tawheed</b> (التوحيد) comes from the Arabic root word \"و-ح-د\" (W-H-D), meaning <b>oneness</b>, <b>unity</b>, or <b>uniqueness</b>.\n\n<b>Tawheed</b> refers to <b>the Islamic concept of monotheism</b>, i.e., believing that there is only one true God — Allah — and He alone deserves worship.\n\n<b>Three categories of Tawheed:</b>\n1. <b>Tawheed ar-Ruboobiyyah</b>: Believing that Allah alone is the Creator, Sustainer, and Controller of the universe.\n2. <b>Tawheed al-Uloohiyyah</b>: Worshipping Allah alone and directing all acts of worship to Him.\n3. <b>Tawheed al-Asma was-Sifaat</b>: Affirming Allah’s Names and Attributes as mentioned in the Qur'an and Sunnah, without changing or comparing them.\n\n<b>In simple terms:</b>\n<li>Tawheed means recognizing Allah's absolute Oneness in His Lordship, Worship, and Attributes.</li><li>Denying Tawheed is the gravest sin (Shirk) in Islam.</li>",
        "bismillah": "",
        "ayah_arabic": "",
        "ayah_translation_english": "",
