    {
        "title": "3",
        "question": "Why is Tawheed important in Islam?",
        "chain_of_narrator": "",
        "authentic_hadith": "",
        "authentic_hadith_arabic": "",
        "clear_answer": "",
        "clear_answer_tag": "",
        "reference_number": "",
        "in_book_reference_number": "",
        "verify_on": "",
        "verification_method": "",
        "logic_source": "Core Islamic Knowledge",
        "logic_authenticity": "",
        "logic_statement": "<b>Tawheed</b> is the foundation and essence of Islam. It is what distinguishes Islam from all other religions.\n\n<b>Why is Tawheed important?</b>\n1. <b>Purpose of creation:</b> Allah created mankind and jinn solely to worship Him (Qur’an 51:56).\n2. <b>Entry to Paradise:</b> Belief in Tawheed is the first condition for salvation in the Hereafter.\n3. <b>Greatest command:</b> The first pillar of Islam — the Shahadah — is built on Tawheed: “La ilaha illallah”.\n4. <b>Opposite of Tawheed is Shirk:</b> Associating partners with Allah is the gravest sin and unforgivable if not repented (Qur’an 4:48).\n5. <b>Unity of Muslims:</b> Belief in one God unifies Muslims across the world under one faith.\n6. <b>Guides worship:</b> It defines how we pray, fast, give charity, and live our lives — solely for Allah.\n\n<b>In simple terms:</b>\n<li>Tawheed is the key to understanding Islam.</li><li>Without it, no act of worship is accepted.</li><li>It strengthens faith, purifies intentions, and builds a direct relationship with Allah.</li>",
        "bismillah": "بِسْــــــــــــــــــمِ اللهِ الرَّحْمٰنِ الرَّحِيْمِ",
