    {
        "title": "4",
        "question": "What does the term “Deen” mean in Islam?",
        "chain_of_narrator": "",
        "authentic_hadith": "",
        "authentic_hadith_arabic": "",
        "clear_answer": "",
        "clear_answer_tag": "",
        "reference_number": "",
        "in_book_reference_number": "",
        "verify_on": "",
        "verification_method": "",
        "logic_source": "Core Islamic Knowledge",
        "logic_authenticity": "",
        "logic_statement": "The Arabic word <b>“Deen”</b> (الدِّين) refers to a complete <b>“way of life“</b> or <b>“system of living“</b>, not just a religion in the limited sense.\n\n<b>Root Meaning:</b> Deen comes from the root \"د-ي-ن\" (D-Y-N), which carries meanings of:\n1. Obedience\n2. Submission\n3. Judgment or accountability\n\n<b>In Islam:</b>\n\"Deen\" is the complete way prescribed by Allah for human life, covering:\n\n<li>Beliefs (Aqidah)</li><li>Acts of worship (Ibadah)</li><li>Social conduct</li><li>Legal matters</li><li>Personal ethics</li>\nThus, Islam as a \"Deen\" is not just faith and rituals, but a full roadmap for living life in harmony with divine guidance.",
